            "creation_date": 1550478955,
            "body": "<p>Your <code>isOnline()<\/code> method will always return <code>false<\/code>. As you haven't returned any value in your <code>try<\/code> block.<\/p>\n\n<p>Find below link to check your internet connectivity<\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://developer.android.com/training/monitoring-device-state/connectivity-monitoring\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Check connectivity (developer.android)<\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>Or, check this below solution:<\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/4009133/9144811\">Check connectivity<\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>After creating your check connection method, use that function in your <code>onHistoryClick<\/code> method on button click.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 54743205,
            "question_id": 54742823
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/6lPKB.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 6877685,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 5285588,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5285588/arka-prava-basu",
                "reputation": 2590,
                "display_name": "Arka Prava Basu",
                "accept_rate": 80
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1550479404,
            "creation_date": 1550479404,
            "body": "<p><code>isOnline()<\/code> sets <code>isInternetConnected = true<\/code> after an async operation. Essentially you are not waiting for that flag to be set/re-set and performing <code>if(isInternetConnected == true)<\/code>. You should chain these two process, ie, perform the second task of <code>get data from server if there is internet/server connection<\/code> after you know from <code>isOnline()<\/code> that the async operation has completed.<\/p>\n\n<p>Running these two dependent tasks independently will not help here.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 54743307,
            "question_id": 54742823
        }
    ],
